RICKY: All right,
let's go, everyone.

26:06.457 --> 26:08.127
Are they sending in
a wheelchair, or a stretcher,
or something?

26:08.127 --> 26:10.167
Yeah. Is somebody
coming in for her?

26:10.167 --> 26:11.127
Uh, no.
I think we're gonna
need to walk her out.

26:11.127 --> 26:12.797
What? Why is that?

26:19.417 --> 26:23.497
♪ You will get
a sentimental feeling

26:23.497 --> 26:26.047
♪ When you hear

26:26.047 --> 26:28.877
♪ Voices singing
Let's be jolly

26:28.877 --> 26:30.497
♪ Deck the halls... ♪

26:38.959 --> 26:40.169
Thank you for
coming to our rescue.

26:40.169 --> 26:43.329
Oh, it's what I do.
Rescue the women.

26:43.329 --> 26:46.919
Okay, well, thanks.

26:46.919 --> 26:49.499
And, uh, I guess everybody
will be back
to get their cars

26:49.499 --> 26:51.379
once they get
Kathy checked in
at the hospital.

26:51.999 --> 26:53.959
So, uh...

26:53.959 --> 26:55.999
I'm off duty. Um...

26:55.999 --> 26:57.499
I'm going to
meet my brothers
at this little diner.

26:57.499 --> 26:59.039
It's kind of
a Christmas tradition.

27:00.709 --> 27:03.539
Would you
care to join me?
Oh. Um...

27:03.539 --> 27:04.829
I don't know.
Maybe.

27:04.829 --> 27:07.289
Come on,
get in the holiday spirit.

27:07.289 --> 27:08.589
They serve a traditional
Christmas dinner all night.

27:08.589 --> 27:10.669
What about
pumpkin pie?

27:10.669 --> 27:11.209
Do they have
pumpkin pie?

27:11.209 --> 27:13.539
Of course.

27:13.539 --> 27:14.459
You can't have Christmas
without pumpkin pie.

27:14.459 --> 27:16.669
Okay. Well, then I'm in.

27:16.669 --> 27:18.089
All right.

27:18.089 --> 27:18.919
After you.

27:21.089 --> 27:22.919
(HUMMING)

27:29.329 --> 27:30.709
Hey, will you
help me out here!

27:30.709 --> 27:32.539
Hey! What are you
doing here?

27:32.539 --> 27:35.249
What am I doing here?
It's Christmas Eve,
you dummy.

27:35.249 --> 27:36.999
Get the food and the gifts
out of the car.
Is everybody here?

27:36.999 --> 27:38.209
Well, not everybody.
Oh!

27:38.209 --> 27:39.379
It took me six hours
to get here.

27:39.379 --> 27:41.999
The traffic was insane.

27:41.999 --> 27:43.089
Oh! Mom!

27:43.089 --> 27:45.039
Hi, George.
Hey, Mimsy.

27:45.039 --> 27:46.789
Merry Christmas.
You want a drink?

27:46.789 --> 27:48.169
Oh, yeah. Sure.

27:48.169 --> 27:48.879
George!
She's on medication.

27:48.879 --> 27:50.999
Ugh.

27:50.999 --> 27:51.749
(GROANS)

27:53.289 --> 27:55.379
(EXCLAIMS)
Well, look at that!

27:59.379 --> 28:01.039
(MOUTHING)

28:01.039 --> 28:02.589
I didn't know
we had company.
(MOUTHING)

28:02.589 --> 28:04.589
You are so pretty!

28:04.589 --> 28:07.379
I mean, darling,
you are really pretty!

28:07.379 --> 28:07.629
Is this your wife?

28:09.129 --> 28:11.709
Uh, I was.

28:11.709 --> 28:13.329
Oh, so was she.

28:13.329 --> 28:14.499
I thought this was
a family dinner.

28:14.499 --> 28:15.789
That's tomorrow night.
Over at Amy's.

28:15.789 --> 28:17.459
And I'm not invited,

28:17.459 --> 28:20.499
so we thought we'd
have our Christmas
tonight.

28:20.499 --> 28:23.289
I, uh, dropped
Tom off with Grace
at the hospital

28:23.289 --> 28:24.829
and then we're
picking them up later,

28:24.829 --> 28:26.329
and then we're
going to church,

28:26.329 --> 28:27.089
and I think
I'll go change.

28:28.829 --> 28:30.209
Tomorrow night?

28:30.209 --> 28:31.879
It's Christmas Eve.

28:31.879 --> 28:33.829
We've always
gotten together on
Christmas Eve.

28:33.829 --> 28:36.249
Hey, not my idea,
it was your
daughter's idea.

28:36.249 --> 28:37.459
And by the way,
your girlfriend's not invited
tomorrow night either.

28:37.459 --> 28:39.829
Oh, yes she is!

28:39.829 --> 28:42.289
We're doing
family dinner tonight

28:42.289 --> 28:43.419
and then tomorrow night,
we're spending Christmas
together.

28:43.419 --> 28:45.039
Not at Amy's.
This totally...

28:45.039 --> 28:47.209
Sucks.

28:47.209 --> 28:49.169
I'm going to go
put Robie down.

28:49.169 --> 28:51.919
Oh, that woman
is such a whiner.
I mean...

28:51.919 --> 28:54.629
I thought she would
never shut up
about the traffic.

28:54.629 --> 28:57.039
I mean, six hours
in a car with that woman.

28:57.039 --> 28:58.249
Ugh!

28:58.249 --> 29:00.129
Merry Christmas, indeed.

29:02.789 --> 29:03.539
(FRUSTRATED SIGH)

29:07.289 --> 29:08.419
Are they gone?

29:08.419 --> 29:08.499
Afraid not.

29:09.829 --> 29:12.209
She wasn't supposed to
be here till tomorrow.

29:12.209 --> 29:14.709
I guess Amy didn't
make that clear.

29:14.709 --> 29:16.829
Guess my Christmas
present to you is
just gonna have to wait.

29:16.829 --> 29:18.629
Mine as well.

29:18.629 --> 29:19.629
Guess we missed our
window of opportunity.

29:21.419 --> 29:21.499
Mmm.

29:24.039 --> 29:25.249
Merry Christmas.

29:25.249 --> 29:26.459
(CHUCKLES)
Merry Christmas.

29:28.709 --> 29:32.129
I've got an hour or so
before I have to
pick up Grace.

29:32.129 --> 29:33.459
Anne said she had
some food in the car.

29:33.459 --> 29:33.539
Nice.

29:35.039 --> 29:36.039
Mmm!

29:39.879 --> 29:43.539
Crackers? Gum?
Chips? Cookies?

29:50.129 --> 29:51.329
Yeah, I'll have some cookies.

29:51.329 --> 29:51.459
I'm hungry.

29:56.789 --> 29:58.959
How long have I
been asleep?

29:58.959 --> 29:59.919
A long time, buddy.

29:59.919 --> 30:02.919
Wow.

30:02.919 --> 30:04.089
What's today's date?

30:04.089 --> 30:05.919
It's Christmas Eve.

30:05.919 --> 30:06.709
It's Christmas Eve?

30:12.709 --> 30:14.329
Oh, my God!
Grace!

30:15.289 --> 30:17.499
(RINGING BELL)
Wake up!

30:18.209 --> 30:19.539
What?

30:19.539 --> 30:20.169
He woke up.

30:20.169 --> 30:22.129
What?

30:22.129 --> 30:24.709
Jack. Jack woke up.

30:24.709 --> 30:26.289
Are you sure?

30:26.289 --> 30:28.289
He was talking to me!

30:28.289 --> 30:30.499
Look, Tom,
I know you're just trying
to make me feel better,

30:30.499 --> 30:32.329
but please, you don't
have to make things up.

30:32.329 --> 30:36.669
No. It's true.
He said he wanted cookies.
He's hungry.

30:37.459 --> 30:40.249
You got to believe me.

30:40.249 --> 30:41.459
Okay, Tom,
I believe you.

30:44.589 --> 30:46.499
We're gonna have to
get going to church soon.

30:46.499 --> 30:50.629
I'm staying right here
in case he wakes up again.

30:50.629 --> 30:51.589
Yeah. Okay.

31:02.629 --> 31:06.039
Hi. We're with Kathy.
She's 15.

31:06.039 --> 31:07.749
I think her parents
are here already
somewhere.

31:07.749 --> 31:08.669
Well, get her in here.
We've been waiting
on you.

31:33.039 --> 31:33.379
(ELECTRICITY SURGES)

31:42.625 --> 31:44.415
(CHRISTMAS MUSIC PLAYING)

31:46.750 --> 31:49.830
So you're really
not going to ask me
to marry you?

31:49.830 --> 31:51.710
I got you
a cashmere sweater,
I swear.

31:51.710 --> 31:53.460
That's the same
thing I got you.
Great.

31:53.460 --> 31:56.120
And there's no ring?

31:56.120 --> 31:57.710
(CHUCKLES) Oh, man.
I told you, you have to
say yes to me in private

31:57.710 --> 31:59.290
before I'm giving you
a ring in public.

31:59.290 --> 32:01.080
I don't want to be
completely humiliated.

32:01.080 --> 32:03.210
It's bad enough
my entire family knows
I asked you months ago.

32:03.210 --> 32:04.920
I hope they didn't
tell my parents.

32:04.920 --> 32:07.370
This is why you're
not getting a ring.

32:07.370 --> 32:09.620
All you're getting
is that cashmere sweater
and all my love.

32:09.620 --> 32:11.000
Mmm.
Mmm!

32:11.000 --> 32:12.370
Whatever.

32:12.370 --> 32:13.830
You can't beat going
to that toy store.

32:13.830 --> 32:15.870
That was amazing.
Yeah, it was.

32:15.870 --> 32:18.160
All right.
Let's go in,
I'm starving.

32:18.160 --> 32:20.870
And as soon as I eat,
we are leaving.

32:20.870 --> 32:22.540
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

32:24.080 --> 32:25.250
Come on.

32:25.250 --> 32:26.250
(SIGHS)

32:31.790 --> 32:34.710
Oh, I like this.
It's like
a treasure hunt.

32:34.710 --> 32:36.290
I told you
she'd have fun.

32:36.290 --> 32:37.660
She loves everything.

32:40.330 --> 32:41.790
It's so fun to
give something
to someone

32:41.790 --> 32:43.000
who hasn't
had anything.

32:43.000 --> 32:45.290
As opposed to me?

32:45.290 --> 32:45.960
Well, I did have
a little trouble
shopping for you.

32:45.960 --> 32:46.620
We both did.

32:51.290 --> 32:52.420
Oh!

32:52.420 --> 32:53.920
I get a treasure hunt, too?

32:57.080 --> 32:59.660
I have arrived!

32:59.660 --> 33:00.920
Ready, everyone?

33:00.920 --> 33:02.330
We're ready.
Are you ready?

33:02.330 --> 33:03.960
I don't know.
What's in there?

33:03.960 --> 33:05.460
Well, open it and see.
But, um, watch out.

33:05.460 --> 33:07.120
Is something
going to jump out
at me?

33:07.120 --> 33:08.460
It could,
you never know.

33:08.460 --> 33:10.830
All right.
On the count of three.

33:12.120 --> 33:15.290
One, two, three.

33:17.160 --> 33:18.420
(MEWING)
(CHLOE GASPING)

33:21.250 --> 33:23.830
A kitten!
You got me a kitten!

33:23.830 --> 33:25.580
Didn't you say
you wanted a kitten?

33:25.580 --> 33:27.830
Only all my life.

33:27.830 --> 33:29.750
I know you'll take
good care of her.

33:29.750 --> 33:30.750
What are you
going to name her?

33:31.830 --> 33:33.250
Patches.

33:33.250 --> 33:35.250
You never
got me a kitten.

33:35.250 --> 33:36.040
Go find your gift.
Uh, I don't
want a kitten.

33:36.040 --> 33:37.790
I know that.

33:43.250 --> 33:46.250
Thank you so much.

33:46.250 --> 33:50.080
Thank you for everything.
You saved my life.

33:50.080 --> 33:51.750
And the kitten's life, too.
She's a rescue.

33:57.080 --> 33:58.920
Merry Christmas, Patches.

33:58.920 --> 34:00.920
Just stay out of my den.
Oh, yeah.

34:00.920 --> 34:03.540
(BLUESY CHRISTMAS
MUSIC PLAYING)

34:06.540 --> 34:08.420
Always wondered
what the box step was.

34:08.420 --> 34:09.420
(CHUCKLES)
It's a box.

34:11.330 --> 34:15.000
Two, three, four.
Uh-oh. Wrong way.
(CHUCKLES)

34:16.870 --> 34:18.120
Just like old times.

34:18.120 --> 34:21.000
It's nothing
like old times.

34:21.000 --> 34:22.870
It's nice to have the girls
out of the house, isn't it?

34:22.870 --> 34:25.330
I hope Sugar Plum
is enjoying a big
Italian Christmas.

34:25.330 --> 34:26.540
I'm sure she is.
(CHUCKLES)

34:29.370 --> 34:31.420
And if she isn't...
BOTH: We don't have to
hear about it.

34:32.370 --> 34:33.870
(CHUCKLING)

34:33.870 --> 34:35.660
Thanks for sharing
dinner with Kathleen.

34:35.660 --> 34:37.460
Yeah, I saw her in
her Santa's helper suit.

34:37.460 --> 34:41.330
She looked like she
needed something to eat.

34:41.330 --> 34:43.040
I'm sorry if I
interrupted anything.

34:43.040 --> 34:45.460
Are you?
No. (CHUCKLES)

34:45.460 --> 34:47.000
Eh. There's always New Year's.

34:47.870 --> 34:49.210
Merry Christmas, Anne.

34:49.210 --> 34:50.370
Merry Christmas.

34:50.370 --> 34:50.460
(GLASSES CLINK)

34:55.330 --> 34:56.330
(CAR HONKING)

34:59.080 --> 35:00.460
Holy smokes!

35:07.250 --> 35:08.580
Did you know
about this?

35:08.580 --> 35:10.460
Know about it?
He let us pick it out.

35:10.460 --> 35:12.870
Yeah, only I picked out
something else
and so did Henry

35:12.870 --> 35:14.500
and your dad went crazy
and got this!

35:14.500 --> 35:15.420
This is insane!

35:32.660 --> 35:35.330
Merry Christmas.
Merry Christmas.

35:35.330 --> 35:36.920
Cleared it with your
parents, not to worry.

35:38.750 --> 35:39.830
(SCREAMS)
This is crazy!

35:39.830 --> 35:41.660
Insane!

35:42.710 --> 35:44.660
Whoa!

35:44.660 --> 35:45.790
Thank you,
thank you,
thank you!

35:45.790 --> 35:48.620
Thank you,
thank you,
thank you!

35:48.620 --> 35:50.620
BEN: Nice touch, Dad.
This is unbelievable.

35:54.210 --> 35:55.830
(MOUTHING)

35:55.830 --> 35:57.920
Hey, you're
graduating this year.

35:57.920 --> 36:01.210
Who knows where
you're gonna be
next Christmas?

36:01.210 --> 36:03.370
Maybe home,
maybe halfway
around the world.

36:03.370 --> 36:05.250
So enjoy it.

36:05.250 --> 36:07.250
And you buy
the next one.

36:07.250 --> 36:09.500
Thank you, Dad.
This is the best
Christmas ever.

36:09.500 --> 36:11.920
Come here, Mom.
Oh, don't make me cry!

36:13.540 --> 36:14.660
Merry Christmas!
Merry Christmas!

36:32.500 --> 36:33.540
(GASPS)

36:37.500 --> 36:39.000
How did you get this in here?

36:39.000 --> 36:40.080
When did you
get this in here?

36:40.080 --> 36:41.790
Wasn't me.
Must have been Santa.

36:47.710 --> 36:49.040
Merry Christmas, Ricky.

36:49.040 --> 36:49.160
Merry Christmas.

36:52.290 --> 36:56.080
I am telling you,
he woke up!

36:58.000 --> 37:00.040
Wake up, damn it!
It's Christmas.

37:00.040 --> 37:01.250
Tom, we have to go.

37:01.250 --> 37:03.250
Jack's dad is
expecting us at church,

37:03.250 --> 37:04.920
and then he and Jack's mom
will come back over here.

37:04.920 --> 37:07.580
But he was awake!

37:07.580 --> 37:09.920
He asked for cookies!

37:10.750 --> 37:12.460
Jack, you want cookies?

37:13.790 --> 37:15.580
Cookies? Yeah.

37:18.710 --> 37:20.370
(RINGING BELL)
Thank you! Thank you!

37:21.250 --> 37:22.870
Hi! Hi!

37:22.870 --> 37:23.830
I love you!

37:23.830 --> 37:25.120
Okay. I love you, too.

37:25.120 --> 37:27.000
Jack, are you okay?

37:27.000 --> 37:29.120
Yeah. I'm a little thirsty.
You're thirsty? Thirsty? Okay.

37:29.120 --> 37:31.290
He needs water.
Someone get him water!
Stat! Please, water, water!

37:31.290 --> 37:33.750
Can we get some water
in here, please?

37:33.750 --> 37:36.460
We, uh, we're here with Jack,
we've got some good news,
get over here.

37:37.330 --> 37:39.160
What's the good news?

37:39.160 --> 37:40.500
Jack, you've been
in a coma.

37:40.500 --> 37:42.500
Did we win?
Uh...

37:44.080 --> 37:46.040
Yeah... Yeah, we did.

37:46.040 --> 37:47.120
Merry Christmas.

37:49.540 --> 37:51.250
It's Christmas?
Yeah.

37:51.250 --> 37:52.870
It's the best
Christmas ever.

37:56.960 --> 37:57.250
It's a miracle!

38:10.620 --> 38:12.620
You ready?

38:14.160 --> 38:15.620
Yeah. I am.

38:16.920 --> 38:18.500
Thank you.

38:18.500 --> 38:19.500
Merry Christmas.

38:20.080 --> 38:21.540
Call me.

38:31.460 --> 38:32.660
Meet your parents,
baby girl.

38:35.500 --> 38:36.960
Thank you, Kathy.
Thank you.

38:40.960 --> 38:42.790
I'm sorry things didn't go
quite like we planned

38:42.790 --> 38:44.420
and that you
didn't get to see her...

38:44.420 --> 38:46.160
That's all right,
that's perfectly all right.

38:49.040 --> 38:50.210
You did a good job.

38:52.540 --> 38:53.750
Hello,
my beautiful daughter.

38:55.460 --> 38:56.710
Are you okay?

38:58.500 --> 38:59.830
I promise I'll be
a good father to her.

38:59.830 --> 39:02.160
And I promise I'll
be a good mother.

39:02.160 --> 39:03.830
I know you'll both
be good parents.

39:04.750 --> 39:06.000
Merry Christmas.

39:06.000 --> 39:07.710
Merry Christmas, Kathy.

39:07.710 --> 39:10.460
Merry Christmas.
And Happy Hanukkah.

39:10.460 --> 39:11.160
(BOTH CHUCKLING)
Happy Hanukkah.

39:13.080 --> 39:15.830
So...
So...

39:15.830 --> 39:18.920
Do you want to know
what we're
going to name her?

39:18.920 --> 39:22.120
I had this aunt
who was crazy
about Christmas.

39:22.120 --> 39:23.580
She had what she called
a toy store downtown,

39:23.580 --> 39:26.920
but it was really
more of an art exhibit.

39:28.660 --> 39:31.250
Every year on Christmas Eve,
she would leave it unlocked

39:31.250 --> 39:36.250
so anyone who dared
come in, they could take
just a little something.

39:36.250 --> 39:38.870
After she passed away,
Jonathan decided
to keep it up,

39:38.870 --> 39:41.500
keep the tradition going.

39:41.500 --> 39:43.460
(SNIFFLES)

39:43.460 --> 39:45.370
It was such
a beautiful gift
to the community.

39:47.370 --> 39:49.040
She was such
a lovely woman.

39:49.040 --> 39:50.160
Your aunt's name
wasn't Hedy, was it?

39:50.160 --> 39:52.040
Yeah.
SONYA: Yeah.

39:52.960 --> 39:55.120
Hedy.

39:55.120 --> 39:56.660
It means
delightful and sweet.

39:58.370 --> 39:59.540
And that's what
she is.

